product_description: Siemens main breaker kits are used to convert the Ultimate type of main lug load centers to main breaker load centers, or can be used as a replacement main breaker in main breaker type Ultimate load centers. Ultimate load centers are the current load center in production and went into production in 2002. Check the load center wiring diagram for confirmation. Siemens strongly recommends against the use of "used" breakers.  The installation of used breakers in a Siemens panel will void the warranty on the panel.  Siemens does not sell used breakers and has not approved any 3rd party sellers to do so.

product_description: Protect a breaker panel in a load center with this Square D by Schneider Electric QOM2 frame size 150 Amp Double-Pole Main Breaker. Used for overload and short-circuit protection of your electrical system, this breaker is compatible with QO and Homeline load centers, CSED devices and NQOD panel boards rated for 150 - 225 amps. It accepts aluminum or copper #4 - 300 AWG feeder wire. To ensure safety, it is both UL listed and ANSI certified. The ANSI-certified and UL-listed unit is rated for 120/240 VAC and 22,000 AIR. QO circuit breakers have features no other manufacturer can offer. They come in many different sizes and can meet the needs of virtually every function in your home or business. These types of quality, industry exclusive products keep the Square D brand ahead of the competition and are builders' and electrical contractors' first choice in electrical protection.

name: ABB TM2020RCUBK1 200A Main Breaker Load Center • PowerMark Gold Outdoor Panel, 120/240V AC • 20-Space, 40-Circuit Configuration • Includes 3 THQP 20A & 1 THQP 30A Breakers • NEMA 3R Surface Mount
short_description: BUILT FOR OUTDOOR USE – This ABB PowerMark Gold 200A main breaker load center features 20 spaces and 40 circuits in a durable NEMA 3R weather-resistant enclosure. Perfect for residential service entrance applications exposed to the elements.

COMPLETE INSTALLATION KIT – Includes a factory-installed 200A main breaker, three THQP 20A single-pole breakers, and one THQP 30A double-pole breaker. Designed for fast, straightforward installation with reliable performance.

DURABLE CONSTRUCTION – Galvanized steel enclosure resists rust and harsh conditions. Copper bus bar provides excellent electrical conductivity, while the self-adjusting dead-front cover supports long-lasting safety and accessibility.

EFFICIENT WIRING DESIGN – Features full-length neutral bars with 100% split neutral holes on each side, rated for #14–4 AWG. One-piece interior is removable for fast access, and pre-loosened combination screws simplify the wiring process.

VERSATILE COMPATIBILITY – Supports 120/240V AC, single-phase, 3-wire systems with a 22,000 AIC rating. Compatible with GE and ABB THQL, THQP, GFCI, and AFCI breakers. Surface-mounted with top or bottom feed. Closure caps included.
